Not quite rendered obsolete by [Mind Bend](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mind Bend), which has more flexibility but only affects permanents. Not as good as [Spectral Shift](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Spectral Shift), even with the increased cost. Unless you have specific spells in mind to alter (like [Seedtime](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Seedtime)) and need the low cost you're probably better off running Bend or Shift instead of this.  

Regardless, this is a fun little spell and the genesis of many a budding Johnny. It's always fun to watch a deck built with this card, [Magical Hack](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Magical Hack), [Whim of Volrath](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Whim of Volrath), and Mind Bend. Even if you lose, it's probably going to be in some really creative way. For general play though this card is a little too difficult to use effectively.  

@Villano137: That combo doesn't actually work, because [Blue Elemental Blast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blue Elemental Blast) and [Red Elemental Blast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Red Elemental Blast) both require the target to be Red/Blue on declaration, *before* Sleight of Mind can be cast. H... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)

